WEBVTT

00:03.704 --> 00:06.540
Announcer:
LEGENDARY DRIVER CHAMP TRUMAN

00:06.607 --> 00:08.376
HEADS DOWN
GAINESVILLE'S BACK STRAIGHT

00:08.442 --> 00:10.678
AT OVER 220 MILES AN HOUR.

00:10.744 --> 00:13.114
YOU'RE A SURGEON
WITH A SCREWDRIVER, STEVE.

00:13.181 --> 00:16.584
YOU GOT THIS HEAP
OF METAL RUNNIN' QUICKER
THAN A BUNNY STEALIN' CARROTS.

00:16.650 --> 00:20.188
NOW, CHAMP,
I'M NOT GONNA LET ANYONE
OUTRACE YOU TOMORROW.

00:20.254 --> 00:21.655
THAT TROPHY IS--

00:21.722 --> 00:23.957
Monster, sarcastically:
YOU KNOW WHAT, CHAMP?

00:24.024 --> 00:27.027
I THINK THIS
IS GONNA BE YOUR FINAL LAP!

00:31.031 --> 00:33.467
[ENGINE REVVING]

00:33.534 --> 00:36.504
BWA HA HA HA HA!

00:36.570 --> 00:39.039
BWA HA HA HA HA!

00:40.541 --> 00:42.376
[SCREECH]

00:54.655 --> 00:56.557
[ENGINE REVVING]

00:56.624 --> 00:59.327
BWA HA HA HA HA!

01:02.263 --> 01:05.099
UHH! OH! OHH!

01:05.966 --> 01:07.135
NEED A LIFT?

01:07.201 --> 01:10.738
BWA HA HA HA HA!

01:14.275 --> 01:15.409
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:15.476 --> 01:17.077
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:17.145 --> 01:19.580
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:19.647 --> 01:21.014
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:21.081 --> 01:22.250
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:22.316 --> 01:25.253
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:25.319 --> 01:27.121
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:27.188 --> 01:28.556
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

01:28.622 --> 01:31.459
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:31.525 --> 01:32.860
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:32.926 --> 01:34.528
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:34.595 --> 01:37.865
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:39.133 --> 01:40.701
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:40.768 --> 01:44.938
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

01:45.005 --> 01:49.610
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

01:49.677 --> 01:50.978
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:51.044 --> 01:52.446
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:52.513 --> 01:55.283
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:55.349 --> 01:56.550
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:56.617 --> 01:57.951
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:58.018 --> 02:00.988
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

02:01.054 --> 02:02.856
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:02.923 --> 02:03.957
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:04.024 --> 02:06.560
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

02:06.627 --> 02:10.063
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:10.130 --> 02:13.434
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
WARNER BROS. ANIMATION TV

02:23.577 --> 02:24.512
SANDWICH?

02:24.578 --> 02:27.080
SCOOB,
I'M DRIVING A RACE CAR.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.317
THERE'S NO POSSIBLE WAY
I CAN EAT A--

02:29.383 --> 02:31.952
LIKE, MAYBE JUST A BITE.

02:32.019 --> 02:33.421
[CHUCKLES]

02:34.955 --> 02:37.491
Daphne: ARE YOU OK, SHAGGY?

02:37.558 --> 02:39.893
CAR'S DRIVING
LIKE A DREAM.

02:43.231 --> 02:44.832
HOW'S IT GOING, VELMA?

02:44.898 --> 02:46.467
QUIET! GREAT.

02:46.534 --> 02:49.837
NOW I HAVE TO START
MY SAFE DRIVER CHECKLIST
ALL OVER:

02:49.903 --> 02:52.072
HANDS POSITION--CHECK,

02:52.139 --> 02:54.007
MIRRORS--CHECK,

02:54.074 --> 02:55.809
BREATHE--AHH-OOH...

02:55.876 --> 02:57.044
CHECK.

02:57.110 --> 02:58.746
Daphne: VELMA,
YOU'RE DOIN' GREAT.

02:58.812 --> 03:01.782
TELL ME AGAIN
WHY I HAVE TO DRIVE
INSTEAD OF FRED?

03:01.849 --> 03:04.017
I HAVE TO PRACTICE
FOR THIS WEEKEND'S RACE.

03:04.084 --> 03:05.753
TOMORROW'S GAINESVILLE 500

03:05.819 --> 03:08.289
IS THE BIGGEST RACE
I'VE EVER QUALIFIED FOR.

03:09.757 --> 03:10.791
[CRASH]

03:12.793 --> 03:14.695
AND...RESET.

03:14.762 --> 03:15.796
[BLEEDLE-LE-DEEP]

03:27.441 --> 03:29.176
LET'S GET TO WORK, GUYS.

03:29.243 --> 03:31.712
I WANT EVERY INCH
OF THIS RACE CAR
CHECKED, CLEANED,

03:31.779 --> 03:34.815
FILLED, LUBED, BOLTED,
TIGHTENED, AND POLISHED.

03:34.882 --> 03:36.149
LET'S GO.

03:36.216 --> 03:37.585
SCOOB AND I
WILL GET
THE TOOL CHEST.

03:37.651 --> 03:39.720
Daphne: CAREFUL,
SHAGGY, IT'S--

03:39.787 --> 03:41.121
WHOA!
[CRASH]

03:41.188 --> 03:42.155
HEAVY.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.991
YOU'RE A CREW CHIEF?!

03:44.057 --> 03:45.225
YOU'VE
GOT EVERYTHING THERE

03:45.293 --> 03:47.094
BUT YOUR BLOW-DRYERS,
GIRLIE GIRL!

03:47.160 --> 03:48.329
MATT FURY'S MY NAME,

03:48.396 --> 03:49.763
AND YOU WATCH YOURSELF
AROUND HERE!

03:49.830 --> 03:52.866
I'M CREW CHIEF
FOR THE RICKY BURDICK.

03:52.933 --> 03:54.268
WHO?

03:54.335 --> 03:55.736
WHO?!! AH,
YOU'LL LEARN HIS NAME

03:55.803 --> 03:57.638
WHEN YOU SEE IT ON TOP
OF THE LEADER BOARD.

03:57.705 --> 03:59.673
NOBODY'S
BEATIN' MY DRIVER!

03:59.740 --> 04:03.411
THAT GUY'S A COUPLE QUARTS
SHORT OF AN OIL CHANGE.

04:03.477 --> 04:06.179
HOW'S THE CAR, FRED?

04:06.246 --> 04:08.916
FANTASTIC, DAPH.
IT'S AS SMOOTH AS--

04:08.982 --> 04:10.451
Skeleton: HELLO, FRED.

04:10.518 --> 04:12.820
OR SHOULD I SAY...

04:12.886 --> 04:14.822
"GOOD-BYE"?

04:14.888 --> 04:17.591
DAPHNE, YOUR VOICE
SOUNDS KINDA FUNNY.

04:17.658 --> 04:19.827
DO YOU HAVE A COLD
OR--OOH, JEEZ!

04:22.195 --> 04:24.498
JINKIES!
WHAT IS THAT THING?

04:24.565 --> 04:27.200
IT'S EITHER A MONSTER TRUCK
OR A TRUCK MONSTER,

04:27.267 --> 04:28.936
AND, LIKE, I DON'T KNOW
WHICH IS WORSE.

04:29.002 --> 04:31.004
STEP ON IT, FRED!

04:42.049 --> 04:43.617
AAH! AH-OH!

04:43.684 --> 04:46.920
BWA HA HA HA HA
HA HA HA HA!

04:46.987 --> 04:48.622
[ENGINE REVVING]

04:48.689 --> 04:52.025
COME ON, GANG! LET'S GET
THAT SCURRYING SKELETON!

04:56.263 --> 04:57.565
[SCREECH]

04:59.867 --> 05:01.735
WHERE DID HE GO?

05:04.872 --> 05:07.541
WELL, IF IT AIN'T
MY GOOD BUDDY FRED.

05:07.608 --> 05:09.109
IT'S BURR BATSON.

05:09.176 --> 05:11.078
WE RACED AGAINST HIM
IN MEXICO

05:11.144 --> 05:12.646
AT THE
ENDURO SLAM 5,000.

05:12.713 --> 05:14.982
ANY CHANCE
YOU OWN A SKELETON SUIT?

05:15.048 --> 05:18.619
NICE TRY, LITTLE LADY,
BUT BURR BATSON
HAS NOTHIN' TO DO

05:18.686 --> 05:20.988
WITH THE MONSTER TRUCK
THAT'S BEEN HAUNTIN'
THIS TRACK.

05:21.054 --> 05:21.989
HAUNTING?
HAUNTING?

05:22.055 --> 05:23.524
OH, YEAH,

05:23.591 --> 05:26.560
THAT GHOST DRIVER'S BEEN
SMASHIN' UP CARS PRETTY BAD,

05:26.627 --> 05:28.328
KNOCKIN' THE BEST DRIVERS
OUT OF THE RACE.

05:28.396 --> 05:31.999
HECK,
OLD CHAMP TRUMAN RETIRED
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

05:32.065 --> 05:33.667
BUT DON'T WORRY, FRED.

05:33.734 --> 05:37.070
THAT SKELETON DRIVER'S NOT
GOIN' AFTER THE AMATEURS.

05:37.137 --> 05:38.005
HA HA!

05:38.071 --> 05:39.573
LADIES.

05:41.141 --> 05:42.843
JEEPERS!

05:42.910 --> 05:45.245
MAYBE IT'S TOO DANGEROUS
FOR YOU TO RACE THIS WEEKEND,
FREDDY.

05:45.312 --> 05:49.617
LIKE, YEAH,
THE ONLY RACE WE SHOULD DO
IS RACE THE HECK OUTTA HERE.

05:49.683 --> 05:50.851
UH-HUH!

05:50.918 --> 05:52.219
HANG ON, GUYS.

05:52.285 --> 05:53.587
I'VE BEEN TRAINING
FOR MONTHS.

05:53.654 --> 05:55.222
THAT TROPHY IS MINE.

05:55.288 --> 05:58.191
WELL, THEN THAT MEANS
WE HAVE A MYSTERY TO SOLVE.

05:58.258 --> 06:01.361
OH, GREAT, NOT ONLY
DO WE HAVE TO DEAL
WITH A SPOOKY SKELETON,

06:01.429 --> 06:03.964
BUT THIS ONE'S GOT
A DRIVER'S LICENSE.

06:05.265 --> 06:07.334
Daphne:
SO WHERE'S OUR HOTEL?

06:07.401 --> 06:10.203
WE'RE STAYING HERE
AT THE TRACK.

06:10.270 --> 06:13.941
BECAUSE THERE'S A HOTEL HERE
I JUST CAN'T SEE YET...

06:14.007 --> 06:15.342
PLEASE?

06:15.409 --> 06:17.377
Fred:
THE MYSTERY MACHINE
NOW SLEEPS 5,

06:17.445 --> 06:20.881
THANKS TO
A FEW MODIFICATIONS
I MADE.

06:20.948 --> 06:23.016
CHECK IT OUT...

06:23.083 --> 06:25.052
OUR NEW BEDROOMS.

06:26.353 --> 06:28.388
OOPS! WRONG BUTTON.

06:28.456 --> 06:30.591
HELLO...BEDROOMS.

06:32.760 --> 06:34.762
I MEANT TO LABEL
THESE THINGS, REALLY.

06:37.297 --> 06:39.132
EHH, IT COULD BE
A WIRING PROBLEM.

06:42.470 --> 06:44.538
SEE? BEDROOMS FOR 5,

06:44.605 --> 06:46.239
AND EVERYTHING
GOES BACK INTO PLACE

06:46.306 --> 06:47.908
AT THE PUSH
OF A BUTTON.

06:47.975 --> 06:49.176
[CRASH]

06:49.242 --> 06:51.344
HMM. I WONDER
WHAT THAT DID.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.146
LET'S NOT FIND OUT.

06:57.785 --> 07:01.221
HI, KIDS, ARE YOU
BIG RACING FANS?

07:01.288 --> 07:03.156
SURE ARE. I'M JIMMY.

07:03.223 --> 07:04.357
I'M CINDY.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.860
WE HAVE OUR OWN CAR
IN THE RACE.

07:07.828 --> 07:09.763
WELL...
OUR DADDY DOES.

07:09.830 --> 07:12.432
AND HE TAUGHT ME
EVERYTHING HE KNOWS.

07:12.500 --> 07:13.934
YOU'LL ALL SEE.

07:14.001 --> 07:16.804
I'M GONNA BE
THE BEST RACER EVER.

07:16.870 --> 07:18.606
WELL, NOT FOR
A FEW YEARS THERE,

07:18.672 --> 07:20.974
AT LEAST IF
YOU WANT TO BE ABLE
TO TOUCH THE PEDDLES.

07:21.041 --> 07:22.009
[CHUCKLES]

07:23.410 --> 07:25.212
[TV PLAYS]

07:25.278 --> 07:26.880
IS THAT YOUR DAD
OVER THERE, JIMMY?

07:26.947 --> 07:28.348
YEAH, THAT'S HIM.

07:28.415 --> 07:29.483
HELLO?

07:29.550 --> 07:31.519
[SHOUTING
AND GUNFIRE ON TV]

07:31.585 --> 07:33.286
HE SEEMS...

07:33.353 --> 07:34.454
FOCUSED.

07:34.522 --> 07:36.757
VERY FOCUSED. HEH.

07:41.529 --> 07:43.731
[SNORING]

07:47.601 --> 07:50.403
[WHAM]

07:50.470 --> 07:53.006
WHAT IS THAT SOUND?

08:05.719 --> 08:07.054
BWA HA HA HA HA!

08:07.120 --> 08:08.922
FREDDY, DO SOMETHING!

08:10.290 --> 08:11.491
WATCH THIS.

08:16.329 --> 08:18.532
YOU MISSED, MISTER!

08:18.599 --> 08:21.334
AND, YES,
THERE IS SUCH A THING
AS TOO THIN!

08:21.401 --> 08:22.670
WAY TO GO, FRED!

08:22.736 --> 08:24.672
BUT, UH,
HOW DO WE GET DOWN?

08:24.738 --> 08:27.007
HMM. DIDN'T THINK
OF THAT.

08:31.311 --> 08:32.479
SO WHAT
DO YOU THINK

08:32.546 --> 08:33.647
THAT
SPEEDY SKELETON
WAS DOING

08:33.714 --> 08:35.749
HERE IN
THE RV PARK?

08:35.816 --> 08:38.919
IF SOMEONE IS TRYING TO
SCARE OFF THE COMPETITION
FOR TOMORROW'S RACE,

08:38.986 --> 08:41.254
ANYONE AT THE TRACK
COULD BE A SUSPECT.

08:41.321 --> 08:43.256
GANG, I THINK
IT'S TIME WE--

08:43.323 --> 08:45.058
SPLIT UP AND LOOK FOR CLUES.

08:45.125 --> 08:47.427
GOTCHA. WE'LL SEE YA AFTER
THE MONSTER ATTACKS US.

08:47.494 --> 08:49.029
COME ON, SCOOB.

08:51.098 --> 08:53.701
HOW DID HE KNOW
I WAS GONNA SAY THAT?

08:55.502 --> 08:58.772
WELP, IF WE
HAVE TO LOOK FOR THAT
FEROCIOUS 4-WHEELER,

08:58.839 --> 09:00.608
NO SENSE DOIN' IT
ON AN EMPTY STOMACH.

09:00.674 --> 09:02.275
EH HEE HEE HEE HEE HEE!

09:02.342 --> 09:03.543
OOH, SHAGGY!

09:07.180 --> 09:11.051
SCOOBY-DOO, NOW
THAT'S MY KIND OF CLUE.

09:20.828 --> 09:24.297
Shaggy: SO...MUCH...
FREE FOOD...

09:24.364 --> 09:26.333
WE NEED HELP
CARRYING ALL THIS.

09:26.399 --> 09:28.068
UH-HUH, UH-HUH, UH-HUH.

09:28.135 --> 09:29.102
CAR!

09:29.169 --> 09:30.337
FRED'S CAR!

09:31.404 --> 09:33.674
UGH! UHH!
ARGH!

09:33.741 --> 09:36.009
BWA HA HA HA HA!

09:36.076 --> 09:38.011
BWA HA HA HA HA!

09:38.078 --> 09:40.047
[TEETH CHATTERING]

09:42.215 --> 09:43.751
HEY, WHAT'S THIS?

09:43.817 --> 09:45.919
JUST A HUNCH,
BUT I'LL BET IT'S THE CAR

09:45.986 --> 09:47.821
JIMMY AND CINDY'S DAD RACES.

09:47.888 --> 09:49.556
QUICK THINKING, FRED.

09:49.623 --> 09:53.627
BUT, YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS SOMETHING ODD
ABOUT THEIR DAD. AAH!

09:53.694 --> 09:55.295
I'LL SAVE YOU!

09:55.362 --> 09:56.463
FREDDY, STOP!

09:56.529 --> 09:58.565
IT'S JUST
A CRASH TEST DUMMY.

09:58.632 --> 09:59.667
OH, HEH...

09:59.733 --> 10:01.534
I KNEW THAT.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.436
A CRASH TEST DUMMY?

10:03.503 --> 10:05.505
WHAT'S IT DOING HERE?

10:05.572 --> 10:07.941
AAH!
WHEH-HOO!

10:13.613 --> 10:14.682
YIKES!

10:14.748 --> 10:16.183
WHOA! UHH!

10:23.390 --> 10:25.192
WHEW! THAT
WAS A CLOSE ONE.

10:25.258 --> 10:27.795
SCOOB AND I
NEARLY BECAME
A TASTY TRUCK-A-BOB.

10:27.861 --> 10:29.663
YEAH, TRUCK-A-BOB.

10:29.730 --> 10:31.799
HOLD ON THERE, SHAGGY.

10:31.865 --> 10:35.068
I DON'T THINK THE MONSTER
WAS AFTER THE 2 OF YOU.

10:35.135 --> 10:37.304
VROOM! VROOM!

10:37.370 --> 10:38.839
VUH-UHH VROOM!

10:40.240 --> 10:42.009
TRYIN' OUT
NEW DRIVERS, HUH?

10:42.075 --> 10:43.576
THEY CAN'T BE ANY WORSE
THAN YOU!

10:43.643 --> 10:45.478
OH, GO TORQUE SOMETHING.

10:45.545 --> 10:47.647
HYUHHH!

10:47.715 --> 10:49.116
HEY, THERE, JIMMY.

10:49.182 --> 10:51.451
UH, CAN I GET YOU
SOME PHONE BOOKS
TO SIT ON?

10:51.518 --> 10:53.453
AW, MAN.

10:53.520 --> 10:54.888
CAREFUL, KIDS,
YOU'RE SITTING

10:54.955 --> 10:56.957
IN ONE
POWERFUL PIECE
OF MACHINERY.

10:57.024 --> 10:59.659
HEY, WE KNOW ALL ABOUT CARS.

11:00.794 --> 11:03.430
WELL, BECAUSE OF OUR DAD.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.332
YOU'LL FIND OUT
DURING THE RACE.

11:05.398 --> 11:07.801
COME ON, CINDY.

11:10.037 --> 11:12.339
DRIVERS, TO YOUR CARS!

11:12.405 --> 11:14.274
THE RACE IS ABOUT TO BEGIN!

11:14.341 --> 11:16.443
WISH ME LUCK, GANG!

11:16.509 --> 11:17.911
IT'S TIME TO RIDE.

11:23.183 --> 11:26.854
HEY, FRED,
THE GAS PEDAL'S
THE ONE ON THE RIGHT,

11:26.920 --> 11:30.357
NOT THAT IT'LL
DO YOU ANY GOOD!
HA HA HA HA!

11:39.632 --> 11:40.968
Announcer:
THE GREEN FLAG IS OUT!

11:41.034 --> 11:44.704
RACING IS UNDERWAY
IN THE GAINESVILLE 500!

11:46.606 --> 11:49.276
HERE COMES FRED!

11:51.711 --> 11:54.714
OK, FRED'S ABOUT
TO ROLL IN.

11:54.782 --> 11:57.384
GUYS, WE NEED TO DO THIS
IN UNDER 10 SECONDS.

11:57.450 --> 12:01.554
HEY, GIRLIE,
YOU GONNA USE A CURLING IRON
ON THE LUG NUTS? HA HA HA!

12:01.621 --> 12:06.493
CURLING IRON JOKES
SHOULD NOT BE MADE BY MEN
WITH RIDICULOUS HAIRSTYLES!

12:07.761 --> 12:08.962
NEVER MIND.

12:10.530 --> 12:11.464
[JACK CRANKING]

12:11.531 --> 12:12.465
[WHIRRING]

12:12.532 --> 12:13.733
[JACK CRANKING]

12:14.667 --> 12:15.602
[JACK CRANKING]

12:15.668 --> 12:16.870
[WHIRRING]

12:18.338 --> 12:20.774
DING-DANG IT!
WHATEVER IT TAKES,

12:20.841 --> 12:22.575
FRED AIN'T GONNA
BEAT MY RICKY!

12:22.642 --> 12:26.479
HMM! THAT GUY
SURE WOULD DO ANYTHING
TO HELP HIS DRIVER WIN.

12:26.546 --> 12:31.018
Announcer: AND BURR BATSON
TAKES THE LEAD!

12:40.460 --> 12:43.163
Daphne: FRED, YOU
HAVE TO GET OUT OF THERE!

12:43.230 --> 12:45.966
OK, DAPH, I'M COMING
INTO THE PIT AREA.

12:46.033 --> 12:48.802
Skeleton:
THAT'S WHAT YOU THINK.

12:52.940 --> 12:54.641
UH...DAPHNE?

12:54.707 --> 12:58.611
YOU DIDN'T HAPPEN TO
INSTALL AN AUTOPILOT
WHEN I WASN'T LOOKING?

12:58.678 --> 13:01.248
OH, NO! FRED'S
LOST CONTROL OF HIS CAR!

13:01.314 --> 13:03.416
HE'LL LOSE CONTROL
OF HIS STOMACH

13:03.483 --> 13:06.186
WHEN HE SEES WHAT I'VE
GOT PLANNED FOR HIM.

13:06.253 --> 13:09.356
WANT TO KNOW THE BEST WAY
TO SHAVE WEIGHT
OFF A CAR, FRED?

13:09.422 --> 13:11.791
A CRASH DIET!

13:29.142 --> 13:31.411
FRED'S OUT OF CONTROL!

13:31.478 --> 13:33.246
WE HAVE TO SAVE HIM!

13:33.313 --> 13:34.882
WE HAVE TO HEAD OUT
ON THE TRACK!

13:34.948 --> 13:36.850
AND, LIKE, HOW DO WE
GET OUT THERE?

13:38.518 --> 13:39.552
[ENGINE STARTING]

13:39.619 --> 13:40.854
HEY! THAT'S OUR CAR!!

13:40.921 --> 13:42.589
OOPS! HEH HEH.
WE'RE IN THE WRONG CAR.

13:42.655 --> 13:44.457
WE'LL GET OUT
RIGHT NOW.

13:44.524 --> 13:45.525
FLOOR IT.

13:45.592 --> 13:46.459
[SCREECH]

13:46.526 --> 13:47.961
[DAPHNE SCREAMS]

13:48.028 --> 13:50.463
JINKIES,
THIS CAR IS FAST.

13:50.530 --> 13:52.399
OK, UM...

13:52.465 --> 13:54.101
SAFE DRIVER CHECKLIST:

13:54.167 --> 13:56.503
UM, HANDS AT 10 AND 2--

13:56.569 --> 13:57.504
CHECK,

13:57.570 --> 13:59.706
UH, MIRRORS--CHECK,

13:59.772 --> 14:02.876
3--I'LL DO IT LATER.

14:08.916 --> 14:10.617
AH! SORRY!

14:10.683 --> 14:12.886
PARDON ME. LOOK OUT! DEH-OW!

14:12.953 --> 14:14.955
WE'VE GOT CATCH UP
TO HIM.

14:24.131 --> 14:26.299
Smash Mouth: * HEY *

14:26.366 --> 14:29.669
* SO YOU WANNA PLAY? *

14:29.736 --> 14:33.406
* YOU'LL SEE MY GAME'S ON FIRE *

14:33.473 --> 14:36.944
* BUT WE DON'T
PLAY THE SAME GAME *

14:37.010 --> 14:39.379
* YOU'LL SEE
I'M GREEDY FOR SPEED *

14:39.446 --> 14:44.317
* AND NEUTRAL
MEANS NOTHIN' TO ME *

14:44.384 --> 14:47.921
* SO IF THAT'S YOUR DESIRE *

14:47.988 --> 14:49.722
* WE'LL GET ALONG FAMOUSLY *

14:49.789 --> 14:51.224
* BUT ONE THING *

14:51.291 --> 14:53.326
* I LIKE TO LEAD *

14:53.393 --> 14:57.130
* I LIGHT 'EM UP
BEFORE THE MOTOR STARTS *

14:57.197 --> 15:00.500
* I GO SO FAST
THAT I COULD NEVER STOP *

15:00.567 --> 15:03.370
* LOOK UNDER THE HOOD 'CAUSE YOU
DON'T KNOW WHAT I GOT *

15:03.436 --> 15:05.838
* I'M A MOVING VIOLATION, BABY *

15:05.905 --> 15:07.074
* HOT, HOT *

15:07.140 --> 15:08.375
* HOT, HOT *

15:08.441 --> 15:09.609
* HIGHWAY *

15:09.676 --> 15:11.144
* THAT'S MY SCENE *

15:11.211 --> 15:14.214
* I MAY LOOK LIKE A BLUR
WHEN YOU SEE ME *

15:14.281 --> 15:16.116
* AND I MEAN,
I'M FLIRTIN' WITH DISASTER *

15:16.183 --> 15:18.051
* I'M A MASTER OF Gs *

15:18.118 --> 15:19.886
* GOIN' FASTER, GONNA PASS YA *

15:19.953 --> 15:21.221
* GONNA PASS SOME DUST
YOUR WAY *

15:21.288 --> 15:22.789
* AND I'M SAYIN' *

15:22.855 --> 15:26.059
* I LIGHT 'EM UP
BEFORE THE MOTOR STARTS *

15:26.126 --> 15:27.760
* I GO SO FAST
THAT I COULD... *

15:27.827 --> 15:29.829
ENH RAH RAH RAH!

15:29.896 --> 15:31.564
Shaggy: LIKE,
THERE HE IS.

15:33.533 --> 15:35.835
WE'VE GOTTA GET YOU
OUT OF THERE!

15:35.902 --> 15:37.437
I'VE GOT A PLAN!

15:37.504 --> 15:40.507
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY
WILL STRETCH
BETWEEN THE 2 CARS.

15:40.573 --> 15:44.044
I'LL THEN WALK ACROSS THEM
TO YOUR CAR AND SAFETY.

15:44.111 --> 15:46.513
SOUNDS GOOD.

15:46.579 --> 15:47.880
READY, GUYS?

15:47.947 --> 15:49.782
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY
AREN'T HERE.

15:49.849 --> 15:52.752
AT THE SOUND
OF THE TONE,
PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.

15:52.819 --> 15:53.920
BEEP.

15:53.987 --> 15:55.688
I'VE GOT SCOOBY SNAX!

15:55.755 --> 15:57.157
COME ON, SCOOB,

15:57.224 --> 15:59.226
WE HAVE TO HELP
OUR BEST FRIEND:
SCOOBY SNAX.

15:59.292 --> 16:01.128
HA HA--
I MEAN FRED.

16:04.597 --> 16:05.598
STEADY.

16:05.665 --> 16:07.600
STEADY!

16:09.969 --> 16:11.971
FREDDY, GO BACK!

16:16.043 --> 16:19.146
HEY, I CAN STEER AGAIN!

16:20.613 --> 16:21.548
HANG ON, GUYS!

16:21.614 --> 16:22.615
[SCREECH]

16:24.151 --> 16:26.353
HOW DID YOU
REGAIN CONTROL?

16:26.419 --> 16:27.954
I DON'T KNOW.

16:28.021 --> 16:30.523
LIKE, MAYBE
IT WAS THIS THING
THAT I JUST BROKE OFF.

16:30.590 --> 16:35.062
WELL, GANG, I THINK
I HAVE THIS MYSTERY
JUST ABOUT WRAPPED UP.

16:35.128 --> 16:37.630
AND, FOR ONCE,
I'M GOING TO SET THE TRAP

16:37.697 --> 16:38.998
WITH FRED AS THE BAIT.

16:39.066 --> 16:41.501
OOH, THIS SOUNDS CLEVER.

16:41.568 --> 16:43.503
AND MUCH SAFER
FOR ME AND SCOOB.

16:43.570 --> 16:45.238
Velma:
WE NEED YOU BACK
IN THE RACE, FRED.

16:45.305 --> 16:46.673
THANKS TO
THAT MONSTER TRUCK,

16:46.739 --> 16:49.008
JIMMY
AND CINDY'S DAD
HAS TAKEN THE LEAD.

16:49.076 --> 16:51.544
I'M READY TO GO.

16:53.380 --> 16:55.748
I CAN GET THIS CAR
RUNNING AGAIN...

16:55.815 --> 16:57.417
I THINK.

16:57.484 --> 17:00.753
WHOA, DAPHNE,
THIS CAR
LOOKS AMAZING.

17:00.820 --> 17:03.123
YOU FIXED IT,
BUT HOW?

17:03.190 --> 17:07.026
NEVER UNDERESTIMATE
THE POWER OF TEAM SCOOBY.

17:09.529 --> 17:13.566
[CHEERING]

17:13.633 --> 17:15.268
FRED'S HEADED BACK
INTO THE LEAD.

17:15.335 --> 17:18.571
ANY SECOND NOW,
WE SHOULD SEE--

17:18.638 --> 17:21.541
PERFECT. IT'S ALL
PART OF MY PLAN.

17:21.608 --> 17:23.876
RAHHHH!

17:23.943 --> 17:25.745
COME AND GET ME,
MR. BONES!

17:25.812 --> 17:28.681
OK, NOW WE JUST
NEED ONE MORE THING
FOR MY TRAP.

17:28.748 --> 17:30.117
COME ON.

17:30.183 --> 17:32.018
FRED'S
REMOTE CONTROL?

17:32.085 --> 17:35.588
YES, BUT IF I
CROSS THE BLUE WIRE
WITH THE RED ONE,

17:35.655 --> 17:37.390
IT BECOMES
A REMOTE BLOCKER.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.362
[SCREECH]

17:42.429 --> 17:43.830
AAH--

17:43.896 --> 17:45.565
[ELECTRONIC VOICE
WINDS DOWN]

17:49.702 --> 17:51.271
LIKE, HEY, IT STOPPED.

17:51.338 --> 17:53.406
THEY STOPPED. BUT WHY?

17:56.209 --> 17:58.211
Velma:
JUST AS I SUSPECTED.

17:58.278 --> 18:00.480
IT WAS ALL CONTROLLED
BY REMOTE,

18:00.547 --> 18:03.383
AND WHOEVER
IS BEHIND IT WOULD
NEED A POWERFUL ANTENNA

18:03.450 --> 18:05.152
TO BROADCAST
THAT SIGNAL.

18:05.218 --> 18:06.753
THERE HE IS.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.788
FRED, MEET US
AT THE TOWER!

18:17.096 --> 18:19.732
YES, IT'S ME.
I DID IT.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.033
I DID IT ALL,

18:21.100 --> 18:23.770
EXCEPT FOR THE STUFF
MY SISTER DID.

18:23.836 --> 18:24.871
BUT WHY?

18:24.937 --> 18:26.606
I WANTED TO
SHOW EVERYONE

18:26.673 --> 18:29.075
I'M THE BEST
RACE CAR DRIVER
IN THE WHOLE WORLD,

18:29.142 --> 18:32.945
BUT THEY WOULDN'T
LET ME IN THE RACE
BECAUSE I WAS TOO YOUNG.

18:33.012 --> 18:35.448
I PUT TOGETHER
THIS GIANT R.C. RACER

18:35.515 --> 18:38.451
AND MADE UP THE STORY
ABOUT MY DAD
BEING A DRIVER.

18:38.518 --> 18:42.189
IT WAS ME IN CONTROL
THE WHOLE TIME.

18:42.255 --> 18:44.691
BUT, LIKE, WHAT ABOUT
THAT MONSTER TRUCK?

18:44.757 --> 18:48.628
CINDY WAS CONTROLLING THE TRUCK
TO GET RID OF MY COMPETITION,

18:48.695 --> 18:51.030
AND WE WOULD HAVE
GOTTEN AWAY WITH IT, TOO,

18:51.097 --> 18:53.866
IF IT WASN'T FOR
YOU MEDDLING GROWN-UPS.

18:53.933 --> 18:55.735
AND, UH, MEDDLING DOG.

18:55.802 --> 18:58.137
YEAH, MEDDLING DOG.

18:58.205 --> 19:00.373
Announcer: AND THE RACE
ISN'T OVER YET, FOLKS!

19:00.440 --> 19:02.909
TEAM SCOOBY SNAX
IS BACK ON THE TRACK!

19:05.878 --> 19:10.217
Announcer: AND FRED JONES
TAKES THE CHECKERED FLAG

19:10.283 --> 19:13.586
HERE AT THE GAINESVILLE 500!

19:13.653 --> 19:14.887
[CHEERING]

19:16.389 --> 19:19.259
FRED DID IT! HE WON!

19:21.093 --> 19:24.664
[CHEERING]

19:24.731 --> 19:28.000
LET'S CELEBRATE BACK
AT THE MYSTERY MACHINE
WITH A BARBECUE!

19:28.067 --> 19:30.703
NO NEED. WE'VE GOT IT
COVERED, RIGHT, SCOOB?

19:37.344 --> 19:40.280
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

19:40.347 --> 19:43.450
SCOOBY-DOOBY BARBI-CUEY!

19:43.516 --> 19:44.517
[SLURP]
